Use command line parameter '-bg' to specify a background script. Script to 
source may also be specified on the command line. 

For example, to run iatclsh with provided example files with Linux:

    iatclsh.tcl -bg ../test/bg_example.tcl ../test/ia_example_hw.tcl

And for Windows:

    tclsh85 iatclsh.tcl -bg ..\test\bg_example.tcl ..\test\ia_example_hw.tcl


